A calendar is used to regulize your schedules.
A calendar is used to know holidays
A calendar is a system of organizing days. This is done by giving names to periods of time, typically days, weeks, months and years. 
A date is the designation of a single, specific day within such a system. A calendar is also a physical record (often paper) of such a system. 
A calendar can also mean a list of planned events, such as a court calendar or a partly or fully chronological list of documents.
